@node IntroDisclaimer
@title "Introduction and Disclaimer"
We wrote this program for those of you who want to win the lottery.  This is
achieved by taking previous results from the national lottery draw, then
calculating likely sets of numbers to put on your ticket.

For a quick demonstration of this program, try the @{"Demo" link Demo} menu item, then
browse around...

Please Note: We accept no responsibility for damage to computer, disks or
loss of data (or loss of money) through use of this program, or any other
programs on this disk.  This file, NL_Winner and the NL_Extras programs may
not be altered.  The NL.Key KeyFile must not be distributed, and the main
program and associated files must only be distributed if accompanied by
this document.
@endnode
@node Sys
@title "System Requirements"
No special system requirements required.  A standard A500 works (although
some features may be disabled unless you have 1 megabyte of memory).  We do
not have access to an A1200, so this program has not been tested on it.
(However, if AMOS works, this should work)

Memory - 1 Meg (512K will run the program, but some features may not work)
Kickstart/Workbench - All versions (1.3 and 2.05 tested)
Graphics - No special requirements (tested with OCS and ECS)
@endnode
