@node HDInstall
@title "Hard Drive Installation"
Hard Drive Installation
-----------------------

1. Boot up with your hard drive.

2. Double-click on the NL_Install icon (found in the NL_Extras drawer)

This program uses the "Installer" utility, which will take you through the
installation procedure.

3. If there is anything you don't understand, click "Help"
@endnode
@node Error
@title "Error Messages and Requesters"
OUT OF MEMORY
-------------

If you are running NL_Winner on low memory, when you start up the program
you may get a requestor as follows:

   NL_WINNER: Out of memory

Close Workbench | Quit Program

Close Workbench: This will close the Workbench screen, and continue running
the program.  Please Note: It WILL NOT close Workbench if there is a
Workbench-launched program (other than NL_Winner) running.
You are likely to get another error requestor afterwards.  If the program
appears to "hang", press Left-Amiga and A to bring the Workbench window to
the front, chose an option from the requestor, then press the same key
combination to get back to NL_Winner.

Quit Program: This exits from NL_Winner

OTHER ERRORS
------------

Standard error requestors:

NL_WINNER: Please report the following
error and sequence of events leading
to it.  Thankyou!

Error: xx/U006Vx.xx/xxx

Continue                      Quit

Continue: Continues the program, ignoring the error.
Quit: Exits from NL_Winner

Warning Messages:

       WARNING!
Current file will be lost

Continue     |     Cancel

Continue: Continues
Cancel: Does not proceed
@endnode
@node KeyFile
@title "The NL_Winner KeyFile (NL.Key)"
This contains your name and address.  It MUST be in the directory S:NL_Data
to use the full version.  If it is not, or the file has been changed, you
will be presented with the shareware version of the program.

You can use this file with all future verions of the program, unless
otherwise specified in @{"About" link About}.  However, be careful when
using @{"NL_Merge" link NLMerge} - If you want to merge someone else's files with your own,
the KeyFile will also be replaced.

It is a good idea to keep a back-up of this file on another disk in case
something happens to the old one.

DO NOT DISTRIBUTE THIS FILE WITHOUT MY PERMISSION
@endnode
@node HowToUse
@title "Getting Started"
How To Use This Program
-----------------------

Double-click on the NL_Winner icon, the program should then display a title
screen.  After a few seconds this will disappear leaving you with the main
menu.

The directory S:NL_Data is now created automatically if it does not exist,
as is the file Numbers and Week 0.

If it still returns to Workbench at this point, the most likely reason is
@{"memory" link Error}.
Close all unneccessary programs and disconnect all external drives.

Try deleting or renaming the file "Numbers" in the S:NL_Data drawer, as the
program will crash if it is corrupt or has been altered.

If it still fails, first check @{"System Requirements" link Sys}, then return the disk to us together with a stamped addressed envelope.

FOR THE FULL VERSION, THE FILE NL.KEY MUST BE IN S:NL_DATA.

NOTE: DO NOT REMOVE ANY FILES FROM THE NL_DATA DIRECTORY, AS THE PROGRAM
DOES CHECKS ON FILES.  IF INFORMATION IN THEM DOES NOT MATCH UP, OR A FILE
DOES NOT EXIST, YOU WILL BE RETURNED TO WORKBENCH.
@endnode
