@node Prefs
@title "Preferences"
Preferences Screen
==================

Change Comment
--------------

Clicking on this will allow you to enter a new default comment which is
saved with all new files of the type shown in the right-hand box.

Clicking on the two arrows to the right of this option will change the
file.

Change Machine Name
-------------------

Clicking on this option will allow you two enter a new machine name for the
abbreviation shown in the right-hand box.

To change the abbreviation letter, use the two arrows on each side of the
right-hand box. (Possible choices range from A - Z)

Start Show Called On
--------------------

Clicking on the arrows selects which screen to go to after clicking on
@{"Show Called Numbers" link Show} (Default: Menu)

Date Format
-----------

Clicking on the two arrows either side of the current format will change it
to a new format. (Default: dd/mm/yy)

The format is displayed as follows:

dd  - Day (eg 31)
mm  - Month (eg 12)
mmm - Month (eg dec)
Mmm - Month (eg Dec)
yy  - Year (eg 95)
/   - Divider
-   - Divider

Blank Option
------------

Does nothing, you can click on it all day and nothing will happen.

Speech
------

If this is on, the computer will read out any information on most screens as
you go into them. (Default: Off)

Update Files
------------

Clicking on the check boxes to the left of the filenames will select whether
the computer will update that file after clicking on @{"save" link Save} or
@{"Create All" link Create}

(Default: All files updated)

The "Previous Weeks" box stops saving the current week's numbers to a
separate file.  THIS IS NOT RECOMMENDED!  If something happens to any of
your main files, you will not be able to re-compile the previous week data
into all the separate files.  The only use I can think of is if you edit
the main file using @{"Enter Called Numbers" link Enter}, and do not want to save that
data, as it is just a correction.

Reset
-----

Resets the configuration to how it was when it was last saved.

Use
---

Uses the current configuration, but does not save it.

Save
----

Saves the configuration.
@endnode
