@node History
@title "History of this program"

History before version 1.7
==========================

I'm not sure of the exact history before version 1.7, but here is a rough
outline:

* NL_Winner originally started before the Lottery, as a program to generate
six random numbers between 1 and 49. (This feature still exists - see
@{"Prediction" link Prediction} and @{"How to choose your numbers" link Choosing})

* A few days before the first draw, I constructed a rough outline of a new
program, using the numerical keys to choose different areas:

@{"Enter Numbers" link Enter} - Type in the seven called numbers
@{"Prediction" link Prediction} - Show each number in order of popularity
@{"Show Called Numbers" link Show} - A list (2 pages) showing number of
times each number had been called

* I cut the @{"prediction" link Prediction} down to six numbers

* I added @{"load" link Load} and @{"save" link Save}

* The screens were then added (inc. title screen), and the writing positioned

* I added a @{"printer" link Printer} option, and changed all the numbers to the proper
colours

* @{"Random numbers" link Choosing} taken from my earlier "NATIONAL_LOTTERY"
program

* Main (numbers) file now @{"loaded" link Load} automatically

* The previous weeks @{"review" link Show} was added

* @{"Date" link Date} and saving the date with the week's data added

* Showing the date with the week's data added

* More @{"predictions" link Prediction}

* Set and machine @{"inputing" link Enter} added (17-12-94 or 18-12-94?)

* Changed instructions to AmigaGuide® format, and HDInstall to Installer
format.

* @{"Editing" link Editing} files was added (V1.3? - Sent to Virus Free PD)

* @{"Save" link Save} option included saving NL_Set and NL_Mac files

* @{"Load Other" link LoadOther} and @{"Save As" link SaveAs} options added

* @{"Printer" link Printer} option changed from @{"RMB" link Abbrev} to @{"LMB" link Abbrev}.

* @{"Save" link Save} option changed back to just saving the main file, as I
thought it took too long to save. (V1.5?)

* @{"View" link Show} previous weeks data - added set/machine

* Added more @{"Other Files" link OtherFiles} - @{"NL_Set \ Mac" link OtherFiles}
                                                @{"NL_Weeks" link NLWeeks}

* Added "new style" @{"random" link Prediction}

* Replaced automatic @{"saving" link Save}/updating of the @{"Other Files" link OtherFiles} (V1.6?)

Version 1.7 (Distributed as Shareware - Deltrax PD)
-----------

Major update, added these features:

* @{"From File" link FromFile} and @{"Create All" link Create}

* @{"editing" link Editing} of set/machine on previous weeks data

* Changed standard and sleep @{"pointer" link Mouse}, plus added cursor and toggle pointers

* @{"Search" link Search} features (This introduced a problem with editing
which I kept forgetting to correct)

* Added @{"NL_Extras" link NLExtras} programs - @{"NL_Bucket" link NLBucket}, @{"NL_SetMac" link NLSetMac} and @{"NL_LuckyNumbers" link NLLucky}

Version 1.71
------------

Minor update, these bug fixes and changes:

* Speeded up pointers

* Added @{"Printer" link Mouse} pointer

* Added new @{"Other File" link OtherFiles} - @{"NL_FirstBall" link Winning}

* Corrected problem in @{"Create All" link Create}- It was naming the NL_Mac files
NL_Machine

* @{"NL_SetMac" link NLSetMac} improved

Version 1.72
------------

Very minor update:

* Corrected @{"editing" link Editing} of previous weeks data set and machine

* @{"Save" link Save}, when editing a file other than "Numbers", will save
it without bringing up a requestor.  The numbers file can now be saved using
@{"Save As" link SaveAs}

* If the numbers file is not found when loading, NL_Winner will now load a
different file (if found) or create a new one. See @{"Getting Started" link HowToUse}

* Improved @{"NL_BootUp" link NLBootUp} - now it works, and displays random numbers

Version 1.73
------------

General speed-up and bug fix.  Sped up @{"saving" link Save} and @{"predicting" link Prediction},
and fixed the bug where sometimes the computer would lock up after a "49" on
the predictions.

Added @{"NL_Stats" link NLStats} Extras program.  This may be incorporated into
the main program, and may even be used to calculate predictions.

Version 1.8
-----------

NL_Stats is now part of the main program, in @{"Show Called Numbers" link ShowStats}

Added a @{"graph" link ShowGraph} feature to help see how many times each number
has been called.

Added @{"Help" link OLHelp} feature

Version 1.81
------------

* Added @{"Wheeling" link ShowWheel} screen

* Added @{"pull-down menus" link PullDown}

* Changed the @{"show called numbers" link Show} screen to go to a @{"menu" link ShowMenu}

* Changed @{"prediction" link Prediction} to go to @{"Stats" link ShowStats}
or @{"Wheeling" link ShowWheel} screens, when clicking on a 1, 2, 4 or 5
prediction.

Version 1.82
------------

Bug-fixes, and added these features:

* @{"Prefs..." link Prefs} @{"menu" link PullDown} item

* @{"Delete..." link Del} @{"menu" link Pulldown} item

* @{"Printing" link Printer} the @{"Wheeling" link ShowWheel} screen

* Added the @{"Info..." link Info} @{"menu" link PullDown} item

* Added @{"error" link Error} requestors

* Changed "AND" and "OR" to "ONE" and "WIN" when @{"searching" link Search}

Version 1.83
------------

Discovered major error!  When saving or creating all files, the program
crashed.

Also, if you could get it to save, it would crash when trying to
review the week you had just saved.  There is an easy solution to this
problem:  Load up the problem Week file (in S:NL_Data), and change the
first line to NL2.  

All these problems were caused by the new file format.

There were also some other (very much more minor) bug-fixes.

NL_SetMac was not always telling you the best set or machine, so I fixed
this bug. (I also discovered that Virus_Checker thought it was infected by
the "Decompiler Trojan Virus", but I haven't been able to fix this problem
yet.

Added @{"odds of winning" link Odds} to docs

Version 1.84
------------

Various minor additions/bug fixes, including redrawing the lines between
each bar of the graph to make it easier to read.  Added the @{"export" link Mouse} pointer
and you can now get @{"wheeling" link ShowWheel}/@{"stats" link ShowStats} information on the @{"random" link Prediction} numbers.
I also added the new @{"Instant Cash" link CashOdds} @{"odds" link Odds} to the docs.

The shareware data has changed so you can now save the numbers for each week,
do searchs and edits on the previous weeks and edit the whole file (but not
change it).  There is a slight change in the way the program knows which week
number you are on: The registered version counts up the number of numbers and
divides this by 7.  The next week number is one above this.  This would cause
problems when saving weeks out of different files, but it does not allow you
to do this.  The shareware version has a file in the S:NL_Data drawer which
tells NL_Winner what the next week number is.
There is also an advantage of saving the separate weeks while using the
shareware version:  When you register you can use the file @{"NL_Merge" link NLMerge} to
copy the old weeks data over to the new disk, then use @{"Create All" link Create} to
create all the files.  This saves you having to type in all the weeks data
again, or gives you a head start if you were just going to start from the
week you got the full version.

The most major change was the file @{"NL_SetMac" link NLSetMac}.  I stopped
it being detected as infected by a virus, and also changed it so you can
now print the information, and get information on combinations of sets and
machines.

I also added the @{"NL_Extras" link NLExtras} programs @{"NL_Merge" link NLMerge} and @{"NL_Backup" link NLBackup}, and moved @{"NL_Install" link HDInstall}
to the @{"NL_Extras" link NLExtras} drawer.

Version 1.85
------------

I (at last!) added the up/down viewing arrows on the @{"graph" link ShowGraph} screen.

I also added a "fake cursor" on the @{"Enter Numbers" link Enter} screen.  This
is so you can see that you can type in straight away, rather than having to
click somewhere (which will return you to the main menu).  This should
hopefully avoid confusion.  I will eventually change this to a proper cursor.

You can now click anywhere while typing in the numbers, and the program
will remove them from memory, and not update the file(s).

The @{"From File" link FromFile} and @{"Create All" link Create} options can now be clicked at any time before
the machine has been entered, and will cancel any information first.

The @{"Prefs" link Prefs} screen has two additions: An option to change machine
names/abbreviations and an option to stop writing the individual weeks data.

I added the @{"Demo..." link Demo} pull-down menu option.

Version 1.9
-----------

* Re-arranged the @{"pull-down" link PullDown} menus
* Added @{"First and Last week" link Search} option
* Added @{"Show Added" link Enter} option
* Added @{"Clear..." link Clear} pull-down menu
* New file format: NL5.  Contains @{"Last Saved" link Info} date
* Fixed the prediction bug (again!) - It is definately gone now

* Improved @{"NL_Install" link HDInstall}

Version 1.91
------------

* Bug fixes - Mainly the new @{"pull-down menu" link PullDown} options
* Added "Pointless Features" - @{"Speech" link Prefs} (set in Prefs)
                               @{"Hear Data" link HearData} (in @{"Project" link PullDown} pull-down menu)
* I had to change NL_Install and the prefs file format becuse of this.
* Changed Preferences screen - "Printer" is now a checkbox option and the
current settings do NOT print when you click on save (now only on use)

Version 2.0
-----------

* Added a new file - @{"NL_NoBonus" link OtherFiles}
* Changed the registration to @{"keyfiles" link KeyFile}, so the program can be updated as
often as you like (main reason for major version number - easy to remember
so you know which versions the keyfile will work on)
* The name and address of the registered owner is encrypted into the
keyfile - so don't distribute it without permission from me.

Version 2.01
------------

* Changed {"Create All" link Create} so it now checks to see which files need 
updating.  I did this after having to wait about an hour to create all the
files, when the only one which needed doing was "NoBonus".
* Due to this, I had to rename the NL_Set \ Mac files NL_SM x x.  If you
have any of these files saved, you will have to rename them manually.
* The registered owner's details now appear on the title screen, and in the
@{"About »" link About} menu.

Version 2.1
-----------

* Added an @{"Export" link Export} feature to save in different formats.  I might add some
formats for different lottery predictors sometime, or a database format for
the previous weeks data.
* Changed the @{"KeyFile" link KeyFile} format (already!), but older versions will still work
* The @{"requestors" link Error} were not coming to the front, and various other @{"bfs" link Abbrev}
* The @{"printer" link Printer} option has changed - now just press "P" to print!

Version 2.11
------------

Not much change - just @{"bf" link Abbrev}'ed a few things and the printer @{"pointer" link Mouse}
now appears when printing.

Version 2.12 - Release 3 (Erm... haven't decided yet!)
------------

A few very minor problems with the shareware version.

@{"NL_SetMac" link NLSetMac} now recognises the new individual weeks file format (added same
time as NL5)
The temporary storage space for NL_SetMac's data has been changed from
"Ram:" to "T:"
